{"lemma": "آخِرٌ", "slug": "آخِرٌ", "root": "#.خ.ر", "root_slug": "_-خ-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/_-خ-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "آخِر", "root": "أخر", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 155}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 6, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 4}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n372", "n374", "n375"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A2%D8%AE%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "last part", "fa": "پایان", "ur": "آخر", "tr": "son", "id": "akhir", "bn": "শেষ", "es": "último", "fr": "dernier", "de": "letzter", "ru": "последний", "zh": "最后的"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to postpone, to set back, to hold back, to put back, to delay", "examples": [{"text": "إِذَا ٱلسَّمَاءُ ٱنْفَطَرَتْ\nوَإِذَا ٱلْكَوَاكِبُ ٱنْتَثَرَتْ\nوَإِذَا ٱلْبِحَارُ فُجِّرَتْ\nوَإِذَا ٱلْقُبُورُ بُعْثِرَتْ\nعَلِمَتْ نَفْسٌ مَّا قَدَّمَتْ وَأَخَّرَتْ", "english": "When the sky breaks apart,\nAnd when the stars commence to scatter,\nAnd when the seas gush forth,\nAnd when the graves are strewn,\nA soul will know what it has put forward and what it has set back."}]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "outcast, distant, remote"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "back part, hinder part"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "feminine plural of آخَر (ʔāḵar)", "tags": ["feminine", "form-of", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Cognate with Aramaic אחר and Hebrew אַחַר (achár).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n372", "headword_ar": "اخّر", "root": "Axr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K, &c.,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taA^oxiyrN", "text_ar": "تَاْخِيرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) is trans. (S, K, &c.) and intrans.: (K:) as a trans. verb it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He made to go back"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "backwards, to recede, retreat, retire,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "retrograde: he put,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "drove, back: he put,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "placed, behind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "after; back,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "backward: he made to be behind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "posterior,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "last: he made to remain behind, hold back, hang back,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lag behind: he kept,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "held, back: he postponed, put off, procrastinated, deferred, delayed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "retarded: he made backward,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "late: contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qad~ama", "text_ar": "قَدَّمَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ax~araniY", "text_ar": "اَخَّرَنِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilaY mud~apK", "text_ar": "اـِلَى مُدَّةٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He granted me a delay,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "postponement, to a certain term,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "period."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ajl", "text_ar": "اجل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)       -A2-  For its significations as an intrans. verb, see 5, in two places."}], "source_refs": ["K"]}, {"entry_id": "n374", "headword_ar": "اَخِرٌ", "root": "Axr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "[an epithet variously explained]. One says, in reviling, (S, TA,) but not when the object is a female, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aboEada Aall~`hu AlA^axira", "text_ar": "اَبْعَدَ اَللّٰهُ الاَخِرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Th, S, A, &c.,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA=xira", "text_ar": "الا=خِرَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, &c.,) or this latter is wrong, (Meshárik of 'Iyád, Mgh, Msb,) as is also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA=xara", "text_ar": "الا=خَرَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Meshárik of 'Iyád,) meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God alienate,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "estrange, from good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prosperity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God curse, him who is absent from us,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Msb, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "distant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remote:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the outcast; the alienated:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "him who is put back,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cast away:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so says Sh: or, accord. to ISh,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "him who is put back, and remote from good:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and he adds, I think that ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^axiyr", "text_ar": "الاَخِير", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is meant: (L:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the base fellow :"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the most ignoble:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the miserable wretch:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Et-Tedmuree and others:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the last speaker:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Nawádir of Th:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlAxr", "text_ar": "الاخر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is here a metonymy for"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the devil:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lb:) it is a word used [for the reason explained voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aboEadu", "text_ar": "اَبْعَدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] in relating what has been said by one of two persons cursing each other, to the other; (Expositions of the Fs;) and the phrase above mentioned is meant to imply a prayer for those who are present [by its contrasting them with the person to whom it directly applies]. (A.) One also says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA maroHabFA", "text_ar": "لَا مَرْحَبًا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biAloA^axiri", "text_ar": "بِالْاَخِرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [alluding to a particular person,] meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May the place,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "land, not be ample,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "spacious,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "roomy,] to the remote from good."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) It is said in a trad. of Mázin,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a AlA^axiraqado zanaY", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ الاَخِرَقَدْ زَنَى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily the outcast,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he who is remote, and held back, from good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mgh, * TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hath committed adultery,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fornication:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the speaker meaning himself; (Mgh, Msb;) as though he were an outcast. (Msb.) And in another trad. it is said,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmasoA^alapu A^axiru kasobi Almaro'i", "text_ar": "المَسْاَلَةُ اَخِرُ كَسْبِ المَرْءِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Begging is the most ignoble"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[mode of]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "gain of man:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but El-Khattábee relates it with medd, [i. e. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=xiru", "text_ar": "ا=خِرُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] explaining it as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "begging is the last thing whereby man seeks sustenance"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "when unable to gain [by other means]. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "TA", "A", "Msb", "L", "Lb", "Mgh"]}, {"entry_id": "n375", "headword_ar": "اُخُرٌ", "root": "Axr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "back, hinder,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "latter, part:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hindermost,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "last, part: contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qudumN", "text_ar": "قُدُمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muw^ax~arN", "text_ar": "مُوَخَّرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; from which it appears to be distinguished by its being used only adverbially, or with a preposition: and see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=xirN", "text_ar": "ا=خِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$uq~a vawobuhu A^uxurFA", "text_ar": "شُقَّ ثَوْبُهُ اُخُرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino A^uxurK", "text_ar": "مِنْ اُخُرٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K, *)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His garment was rent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "slit, in its back,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hinder, part,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "behind."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taA^ax~ara A^uxurFA", "text_ar": "تَاَخَّرَ اُخُرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He retired backwards"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaA='i A^uxurFA", "text_ar": "جَا=ءِ اُخُرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=xirN", "text_ar": "ا=خِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places."}], "source_refs": ["S"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}